				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Weapon delay<a name="33643"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Apr 8 04 2:30 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>The 20 delay is shorter than the 30 delay.  The shorter the delay the better as long as the damage is as close to the delay as posible.  A damage delay of 10/20 is basically the same as 20/40. The are both a ratio of 2 (20 divided by 10 and 40 divided by 20)  The lower the ratio the better.  The 10/20 is fast but the latter does more damage therefore evens out a bit.  That's why a lot of the two handed stuff has a higher delay but evens out with a higher damage output.  I believe the Wristsnapper is something like 11/18 which is really good.  Like I said, the closer the first number is to the last number the better.. If the first number (damage) is greater than the last number (delay) that's even better but this is the uber items.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
