			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Weapon delay<a name="33682"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Apr 8 04 3:52 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span><blockquote><b>Quote:</b><br><span class="quote">A damage delay of 10/20 is basically the same as 20/40. The are both a ratio of 2 (20 divided by 10 and 40 divided by 20) The lower the ratio the better. The 10/20 is fast but the latter does more damage therefore evens out a bit. </span></blockquote>
<br />

<br />
While true in the most basic sense, in actuality it depends on the placement of the weapon.  In choosing a primary weapon, you generally want to go with a lower delay vs ratio (within reason) because the lower the delay for your primary weapon, the more use you get out of the damage bonus.
<br />
Offhand weapons don't have an applied damage bonus, and you need to try to stick more to the ratio.
<br />

<br />

<br />

<br />
Feydrioron of Rodcet Nife</span></td>
