			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Weapon delay<a name="33696"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Apr 8 04 4:57 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>As an example of the power of a low delay weapon.  There is a weapon called the Moss Covered Twig which is 1 dam 10 delay off hand only.  This used to be both primary and secondary and at the time was the most sought after weapon in the game.  The 1 damage was not important but the delay ment that a warrior would get twice the damage bonus of a 20 delay weapon.  At the time this was so unballancing that SOE nerfed it to be secondary only.
<br />

<br />
So the basic rule of thumb is:
<br />
Lowest delay in primary and best ratio in secondary.  
<br />

<br />
Of course if you are a true bard you will chose your weapon based on looks<img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-1.gif" border="0" alt="Smiley" hspace="2" />.  That is because even though your damage output still sucks, at least you will look good. <img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-1.gif" border="0" alt="Smiley" hspace="2" /> 
<br />
</span></td>
